# Causal DAG for the smoking example (v0.8). Quantified by the BN in
# bayes-network.ttl (causal:basedOn). Genotype is OBSERVED here, so the
# Smoking -> Cancer effect is identifiable by back-door adjustment over Genotype.
#
# For the latent/front-door variant, set sm:Genotype causal:observed false and
# add a mediator sm:Tar (Smoking -> Tar -> Cancer); then `ontorag causal
# identify` reports a front-door adjustment set {Tar}.
#
# Over-claim guard: this DAG is user-supplied. ontorag computes do /
# counterfactual queries ASSUMING it is correct; it does not validate causal
# semantics or discover causation.

@prefix causal: <https://ontorag.dev/causal#> .
@prefix sm:     <https://ontorag.dev/smoking#> .
@prefix rdfs:   <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

causal:model a causal:CausalModel ;
    rdfs:label "smoking" ;
    causal:basedOn <https://ontorag.dev/bn#network> ;
    causal:hasVariable sm:Genotype, sm:Smoking, sm:Cancer .

sm:Genotype a causal:Variable ; rdfs:label "Genotype" ; causal:observed true .
sm:Smoking  a causal:Variable ; rdfs:label "Smoking"  ; causal:observed true .
sm:Cancer   a causal:Variable ; rdfs:label "Cancer"   ; causal:observed true .

sm:Genotype causal:influences sm:Smoking .
sm:Genotype causal:influences sm:Cancer .
sm:Smoking  causal:influences sm:Cancer .
